  <summary date="2004-07-20T16:10:29Z" status="Introduced in House">Honors and recognizes the American labor movement.

Supports the designation of a National Labor History Month.

Urges government officials, educators, the media, and all Americans to observe a National Labor History Month with ceremonies, activities, and programs that encourage reflection on the labor movement's heritage and contributions to the creation and maintenance of a just America.</summary>
